{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5f061e00-ea2a-41c0-ae0a-fe7cef0e8df5","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** these packages:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsofttestingplatform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Enable** the output type (needed for MTP's executable host):\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n   ```\n   — or set `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` manually.\n\n5. Run tests with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly execute the test project binary.\n\n> **Tip:** If you use `dotnet test`, the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures compatibility. If you rely on `.runsettings` or VSTest-specific features (e.g., data collectors), check the [MTP migration docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/unit-testing-mstest-migration) for equivalents — most xUnit features carry over seamlessly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"41c84d7c-2738-4def-8b16-5db24b49007d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":424,"requestId":"4C1A:188DB0:CF98D9:1038E80:6A012933"},"id":"4dfbb1c9-1820-413b-94e3-fe47d68c4016","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:56:28.768Z","parentId":"5e339a06-9bf7-427b-95df-ca5af92b22c4"}
